---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Support - MIDI Volume Control - Field Bureau + Werkstatt"
  description="Get help with MIDI Volume Control. Find answers to common questions and contact support for assistance."
  gradientOverlay="linear-gradient(to bottom, #1a1a1a, #0f0f0f)"
>
  <div class="relative min-h-screen flex flex-col">

    <!-- Breadcrumb Navigation -->
    <nav class="relative z-10 px-6 md:px-12 py-6">
      <div class="flex items-center space-x-2 text-sm text-white/80 drop-shadow-lg">
        <a href="/" class="hover:text-white transition-colors">Home</a>
        <span class="text-white/40">/</span>
        <a href="/midi-volume" class="hover:text-white transition-colors">MIDI Volume Control</a>
        <span class="text-white/40">/</span>
        <span class="text-white">Support</span>
      </div>
    </nav>

    <!-- Content -->
    <div class="relative z-10 px-6 md:px-12 py-12 flex-1">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">

        <!-- Header -->
        <div class="text-center mb-16 animate-fade-in-up" style="opacity: 0;">
          <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-light text-white mb-6 drop-shadow-lg">
            Support & Help
          </h1>
          <p class="text-xl text-white/90 drop-shadow-lg">
            Find answers to common questions or get in touch for additional support.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- FAQ Section -->
        <div class="mb-16">
          <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-light text-white mb-12 text-center drop-shadow-lg">
            Frequently Asked Questions
          </h2>

          <div class="space-y-6">
            <!-- FAQ Item 1 -->
            <div class="border border-white/20 rounded-xl p-6 backdrop-blur-sm bg-white/5 animate-fade-in-up" style="animation-delay: 100ms; opacity: 0;">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-medium text-white mb-3 drop-shadow-lg">
                Do I need a MIDI controller to use this app?
              </h3>
              <p class="text-white/80 leading-relaxed drop-shadow-lg">
                No! While MIDI Volume Control is designed to work with MIDI controllers for hands-on volume control, you can also use the menu bar interface to adjust both system and Apple Music volume manually without any MIDI hardware.
              </p>
            </div>

            <!-- FAQ Item 2 -->
            <div class="border border-white/20 rounded-xl p-6 backdrop-blur-sm bg-white/5 animate-fade-in-up" style="animation-delay: 200ms; opacity: 0;">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-medium text-white mb-3 drop-shadow-lg">
                How do I set up my MIDI controller?
              </h3>
              <p class="text-white/80 leading-relaxed drop-shadow-lg">
                It's easy! Just connect your MIDI controller, open MIDI Volume Control settings, click "MIDI Learn" next to the control you want to map, then move the knob, fader, or button on your controller. The app will automatically detect and map it.
              </p>
            </div>

            <!-- FAQ Item 3 -->
            <div class="border border-white/20 rounded-xl p-6 backdrop-blur-sm bg-white/5 animate-fade-in-up" style="animation-delay: 300ms; opacity: 0;">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-medium text-white mb-3 drop-shadow-lg">
                Can I control system volume and Apple Music volume separately?
              </h3>
              <p class="text-white/80 leading-relaxed drop-shadow-lg">
                Yes! This is one of the key features. You can map different MIDI controls to system volume and Apple Music volume, allowing you to balance your music with other audio sources like Discord, Zoom calls, or system sounds independently.
              </p>
            </div>

            <!-- FAQ Item 4 -->
            <div class="border border-white/20 rounded-xl p-6 backdrop-blur-sm bg-white/5 animate-fade-in-up" style="animation-delay: 400ms; opacity: 0;">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-medium text-white mb-3 drop-shadow-lg">
                Which MIDI controllers are compatible?
              </h3>
              <p class="text-white/80 leading-relaxed drop-shadow-lg">
                MIDI Volume Control works with virtually any MIDI controller that sends standard MIDI CC (Control Change) messages. This includes popular controllers like Akai MPK series, Novation Launchkey, Arturia KeyLab, and many others.
              </p>
            </div>

            <!-- FAQ Item 5 -->
            <div class="border border-white/20 rounded-xl p-6 backdrop-blur-sm bg-white/5 animate-fade-in-up" style="animation-delay: 500ms; opacity: 0;">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-medium text-white mb-3 drop-shadow-lg">
                Does the app affect my Mac's performance or battery life?
              </h3>
              <p class="text-white/80 leading-relaxed drop-shadow-lg">
                No, MIDI Volume Control is designed to be lightweight and efficient. It runs quietly in the background with negligible impact on your Mac's performance or battery life, using minimal system resources and permissions.
              </p>
            </div>

            <!-- FAQ Item 6 -->
            <div class="border border-white/20 rounded-xl p-6 backdrop-blur-sm bg-white/5 animate-fade-in-up" style="animation-delay: 600ms; opacity: 0;">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-medium text-white mb-3 drop-shadow-lg">
                What happens if I disconnect my MIDI controller?
              </h3>
              <p class="text-white/80 leading-relaxed drop-shadow-lg">
                The app continues to work! You can still access volume controls through the menu bar interface. When you reconnect your MIDI controller, it will be automatically detected and your previous mappings will be restored.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Contact Section -->
        <div class="text-center mb-16 animate-fade-in-up" style="animation-delay: 700ms; opacity: 0;">
          <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-light text-white mb-6 drop-shadow-lg">
            Need More Help?
          </h2>
          <p class="text-xl text-white/90 mb-8 drop-shadow-lg">
            Can't find what you're looking for? Get in touch and we'll help you out.
          </p>

          <div class="bg-white/5 backdrop-blur-sm border border-white/20 rounded-2xl p-8 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
            <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-white/10 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-6">
              <svg class="w-8 h-8 text-white" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M21.75 6.75v10.5a2.25 2.25 0 0 1-2.25 2.25h-15a2.25 2.25 0 0 1-2.25-2.25V6.75m19.5 0A2.25 2.25 0 0 0 19.5 4.5h-15a2.25 2.25 0 0 0-2.25 2.25m19.5 0v.243a2.25 2.25 0 0 1-1.07 1.916l-7.5 4.615a2.25 2.25 0 0 1-2.36 0L3.32 8.91a2.25 2.25 0 0 1-1.07-1.916V6.75" />
              </svg>
            </div>

            <h3 class="text-2xl font-light text-white mb-4 drop-shadow-lg">Email Support</h3>
            <p class="text-white/80 mb-6 drop-shadow-lg">
              Send us an email and we'll get back to you as soon as possible.
            </p>

            <a
              href="mailto:midiVol@kohlhofer.com"
              class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-8 py-4 text-base font-medium text-white bg-white/10 backdrop-blur-sm border border-white/30 rounded-xl hover:bg-white/20 hover:border-white/40 transition-all duration-200 shadow-lg"
            >
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 mr-2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M21.75 6.75v10.5a2.25 2.25 0 0 1-2.25 2.25h-15a2.25 2.25 0 0 1-2.25-2.25V6.75m19.5 0A2.25 2.25 0 0 0 19.5 4.5h-15a2.25 2.25 0 0 0-2.25 2.25m19.5 0v.243a2.25 2.25 0 0 1-1.07 1.916l-7.5 4.615a2.25 2.25 0 0 1-2.36 0L3.32 8.91a2.25 2.25 0 0 1-1.07-1.916V6.75" />
              </svg>
              Contact Support
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Footer with black background -->
  <footer class="bg-black py-8 px-6 md:px-12">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto">
      <p class="text-center text-white/30 text-xs tracking-wide">
        <span class="font-semibold">Field Bureau + Werkstatt</span>
        <span class="mx-2">•</span>
        © {new Date().getFullYear()} Field Bureau & Werkstatt LLC. All rights reserved.
      </p>
    </div>
  </footer>
</BaseLayout>
